President Obama called Prime Minister Salam of Lebanon to congratulate him on the Lebanese parliament's approval of the Prime Minister's cabinet. The President praised the leadership of President Sleiman and Prime Minister Salam during the government formation process and their efforts to address the challenges facing Lebanon. He urged that the upcoming presidential elections be held on time and in accordance with the Lebanese constitution. The President emphasized the importance of all parties adhering to Lebanon's policy of disassociation and thanked the Prime Minister for Lebanon's assistance to Syrian refugees. He reassured the United States' commitment to supporting refugees and Lebanese host communities, as well as partnering with the Lebanese government, Armed Forces, and people to promote Lebanon's security, unity, and sovereignty.